Pathways and dropouts - TFH sorted cells

The pathways to consider here

module <- "BTM"
min_gene_in_module <- 5
packageExt <- system.file("extdata", package='MAST')
module_file <- list.files(packageExt, pattern = module, full.names = TRUE)
gene_set <- getGmt(module_file)
gene_ids <- geneIds(gene_set)
dropout_rates <- apply(TFH_UMI, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x > 0))))
vec <- as.vector(dropout_rates)
vec2 <- (vec - mean(vec))/sd(vec)
names(vec2) <- names(dropout_rates)
out <- fgsea::fgsea(gene_ids, vec2, minSize=1,
                  maxSize=500,
                  nperm=10000)
mm <- cbind.data.frame(out$padj, out$size)
mm$topgenes <- out$leadingEdge
rownames(mm) <- names(gene_ids)[as.numeric(rownames(mm))]
mm[order(mm$`out$padj`, decreasing = FALSE),]

TFH sorted cells position study

ensembl = useMart("ensembl",dataset="hsapiens_gene_ensembl")
filters = listFilters(ensembl)
filters[1:5,]
##              name              description
## 1 chromosome_name Chromosome/scaffold name
## 2           start                    Start
## 3             end                      End
## 4      band_start               Band Start
## 5        band_end                 Band End
out <- getBM(attributes = c('external_gene_name', 'chromosome_name',
                   'start_position', 'end_position'),
      filters = 'external_gene_name', 
      values = rownames(TFH_UMI), 
      mart = ensembl)
out[1:5,]
##   external_gene_name chromosome_name start_position end_position
## 1             RNU6-2              19        1021522      1021628
## 2           RNU2-64P               3       73110992     73111182
## 3          RNA5SP508               X       76655009     76655127
## 4          RNU6-519P               8       47979414     47979521
## 5           RNU6-10P               7       92701708     92701814

chromosome 1

par(mfrow=c(2,2))
idx <- which(out$chromosome_name == 1)
gene_ids <- out$external_gene_name[idx]
start_pos <- out$start_position[idx]
end_pos <- out$end_position[idx]
temp_idx <- match(gene_ids, rownames(TFH_UMI))
temp_idx <- temp_idx[!is.na(temp_idx)]
tmp <- TFH_UMI[temp_idx,]
dropouts <- apply(tmp, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x == 0))/length(x)))

width <- end_pos[which(!is.na(temp_idx))] - start_pos[which(!is.na(temp_idx))]
plot(log(width), dropouts, xlab = "Log width of the gene", ylab = "dropout rates", pch=20, cex=0.6)

dropouts <- apply(tmp, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x == 0))/length(x)))
plot(start_pos[order(start_pos)], dropouts[order(start_pos)], pch = 20, xlab = "Start position of genes", ylab = "Dropout rates")

dropouts <- apply(tmp, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x == 0))/length(x)))
plot(start_pos[order(end_pos)], dropouts[order(end_pos)], pch = 20, xlab = "Start position of genes", ylab = "Dropout times width")

dropout_width <- width*dropouts
plot(start_pos[order(start_pos)], dropout_width[order(start_pos)], pch=20)

temp_idx <- match(gene_ids, rownames(TFH_UMI))
temp_idx <- temp_idx[!is.na(temp_idx)]
tmp <- TFH_UMI[temp_idx,]
dropouts <- apply(tmp, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x == 0))/length(x)))

width <- end_pos[which(!is.na(temp_idx))] - start_pos[which(!is.na(temp_idx))]
plot(log(width), dropouts, xlab = "Log width of the gene", ylab = "dropout rates", pch=20, cex=0.6)

dropouts <- apply(tmp, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x == 0))/length(x)))
plot(start_pos[order(start_pos)], dropouts[order(start_pos)], pch = 20, xlab = "Start position of genes", ylab = "Dropout rates")

dropouts <- apply(tmp, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x == 0))/length(x)))
plot(start_pos[order(end_pos)], dropouts[order(end_pos)], pch = 20, xlab = "Start position of genes", ylab = "Dropout times width")

dropout_width <- width*dropouts
plot(start_pos[order(start_pos)], dropout_width[order(start_pos)], pch=20)

Live Cells

###--- Filtering datasets and merging
#- LN
identical(colnames(LiveCells_LN_UMI), rownames(LiveCells_LN_UMI_summary)) # TRUE
## [1] TRUE
LiveCells_LN_UMI_filtered <- LiveCells_LN_UMI[, which(LiveCells_LN_UMI_summary$NUM_GENES >= 400 & LiveCells_LN_UMI_summary$NUM_TRANSCRIPTS >= 750)] 
LiveCells_LN_UMI_filtered <- LiveCells_LN_UMI_filtered[which(apply(LiveCells_LN_UMI_filtered, 1, sum) != 0), ]
#- PBMC
identical(colnames(LiveCells_PBMC_UMI), rownames(LiveCells_PBMC_UMI_summary)) # TRUE
## [1] TRUE
LiveCells_PBMC_UMI_filtered <- LiveCells_PBMC_UMI[, which(LiveCells_PBMC_UMI_summary$NUM_GENES >= 400 & LiveCells_PBMC_UMI_summary$NUM_TRANSCRIPTS >= 750)] 
LiveCells_PBMC_UMI_filtered <- LiveCells_PBMC_UMI_filtered[which(apply(LiveCells_PBMC_UMI_filtered, 1, sum) != 0), ] 
#- Merging
LiveCells_UMI <- rbind.fill(as.data.frame(t(LiveCells_LN_UMI_filtered)), as.data.frame(t(LiveCells_PBMC_UMI_filtered)))
rownames(LiveCells_UMI) <- c(paste(colnames(LiveCells_LN_UMI_filtered), 'LN', sep = '_'), paste(colnames(LiveCells_PBMC_UMI_filtered), 'PBMC', sep = '_'))
dim(LiveCells_UMI) 
## [1]   826 16230
length(unique(c(rownames(LiveCells_LN_UMI_filtered), rownames(LiveCells_PBMC_UMI_filtered)))) # 19,183 genes
## [1] 16230
LiveCells_UMI[is.na(LiveCells_UMI)] <- 0 # NAs - replace NA by 0
LiveCells_UMI <- as.data.frame(t(LiveCells_UMI))

The pathways to consider here

module <- "BTM"
min_gene_in_module <- 5
packageExt <- system.file("extdata", package='MAST')
module_file <- list.files(packageExt, pattern = module, full.names = TRUE)
gene_set <- getGmt(module_file)
gene_ids <- geneIds(gene_set)
dropout_rates <- apply(LiveCells_UMI, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x > 0))))
vec <- as.vector(dropout_rates)
vec2 <- (vec - mean(vec))/sd(vec)
names(vec2) <- names(dropout_rates)
out <- fgsea::fgsea(gene_ids, vec2, minSize=1,
                  maxSize=500,
                  nperm=10000)
mm <- cbind.data.frame(out$padj, out$size)
mm$topgenes <- out$leadingEdge
rownames(mm) <- names(gene_ids)[as.numeric(rownames(mm))]

Live cells position study

out <- getBM(attributes = c('external_gene_name', 'chromosome_name',
                   'start_position', 'end_position'),
      filters = 'external_gene_name', 
      values = rownames(TFH_UMI), 
      mart = ensembl)
out[1:5,]
##   external_gene_name chromosome_name start_position end_position
## 1             RNU6-2              19        1021522      1021628
## 2           RNU2-64P               3       73110992     73111182
## 3          RNA5SP508               X       76655009     76655127
## 4          RNU6-519P               8       47979414     47979521
## 5           RNU6-10P               7       92701708     92701814

chromosome 1

par(mfrow=c(2,2))
idx <- which(out$chromosome_name == 1)
gene_ids <- out$external_gene_name[idx]
start_pos <- out$start_position[idx]
end_pos <- out$end_position[idx]
temp_idx <- match(gene_ids, rownames(LiveCells_UMI))
temp_idx <- temp_idx[!is.na(temp_idx)]
tmp <- LiveCells_UMI[temp_idx,]
dropouts <- apply(tmp, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x == 0))/length(x)))

width <- end_pos[which(!is.na(temp_idx))] - start_pos[which(!is.na(temp_idx))]
plot(log(width), dropouts, xlab = "Log width of the gene", ylab = "dropout rates", pch=20, cex=0.6)

dropouts <- apply(tmp, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x == 0))/length(x)))
plot(start_pos[order(start_pos)], dropouts[order(start_pos)], pch = 20, xlab = "Start position of genes", ylab = "Dropout rates")

dropouts <- apply(tmp, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x == 0))/length(x)))
plot(start_pos[order(end_pos)], dropouts[order(end_pos)], pch = 20, xlab = "Start position of genes", ylab = "Dropout times width")

dropout_width <- width*dropouts
plot(start_pos[order(start_pos)], dropout_width[order(start_pos)], pch=20)

idx <- which(out$chromosome_name == 18)

dropouts <- apply(tmp, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x == 0))/length(x)))

width <- end_pos[which(!is.na(temp_idx))] - start_pos[which(!is.na(temp_idx))]
plot(log(width), dropouts, xlab = "Log width of the gene", ylab = "dropout rates", pch=20, cex=0.6)

dropouts <- apply(tmp, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x == 0))/length(x)))
plot(start_pos[order(start_pos)], dropouts[order(start_pos)], pch = 20, xlab = "Start position of genes", ylab = "Dropout rates")

dropouts <- apply(tmp, 1, function(x) return(length(which(x == 0))/length(x)))
plot(start_pos[order(end_pos)], dropouts[order(end_pos)], pch = 20, xlab = "Start position of genes", ylab = "Dropout times width")

dropout_width <- width*dropouts
plot(start_pos[order(start_pos)], dropout_width[order(start_pos)], pch=20)
